Producing Unique Craft Beer With Excellent Taste And Consistent Quality Batch After Batch
About Crooked Can
Built upon the founder’s passion for craft beer, Crooked Can Brewing Company is a local craft brewery built inside the Plant Street Market located in downtown Winter Garden, Florida. The brewery represents a unique image and creates a cultural following for a way of life. The brand represents a free spirit, laid-back approach but with a purpose.
We produce unique craft beer with excellent taste and consistent quality. The brewing process is monitored under the close personal attention of an award-winning experienced brewmaster to ensure the vision is reached batch after batch using traditional brewing methods and cutting-edge brewing practices. The brewery has an onsite tap and tasting room featuring flagship brands in addition to many other limited editions, seasonal, and specialty batches.
Our Founder
Andy Sheeter
The Story
Crooked Can Brewing Company was founded in 2014 by Andrew Sheeter.  The idea for the company originated out of a Ski trip among great friends to Colorado and visiting some unique breweries, the idea of Crooked Can was born.  The theme to this unique concept was to create a social gathering place for family and friends.  The brand represents a free spirit, laid back approach, but with a purpose.  We produce quality craft beer consistently, with excellent taste and unique quality.  Crooked Can Brewing Company sit’s inside Plant Street Market in historic Winter Garden.  The brewery has an onsite tap and tasting room and a brand new ‘Barrel Room’ featuring seasonal and specialty batches of our award winning craft beer.
